# {{CMD_PREFIX}}-bootstrap

Model/effort: Sonnet / medium.

Brings a clean environment up to a working state. Reads the workspace manifest and
installs everything needed to coordinate the system from this machine.

## Steps
1. OPEN-lite: read the operating contract and `brain.manifest.json`; state which
   environment is being bootstrapped.
2. Install the toolchain the project declares (language runtimes, package managers, CLIs).
3. Clone every repo listed in the manifest `app_repos`, plus the brain repo itself, into
   the workspace layout the project expects.
4. Install dependencies for each repo the way that repo installs them.
5. Install the session hooks (SessionStart / SessionEnd) so the ritual runs automatically.
6. Verify the environment: run a smoke check per repo (build or test) and report results.
   Never stage secrets or live config.

## Done when
The toolchain is installed, all manifest repos are cloned and ready, hooks are active,
and smoke checks pass.
